00:01:03.613 --> 00:01:07.356
Because, of course, if it's a large party,
then no one would be surprised.

00:01:07.356 --> 00:01:09.596
But if it's a small number of people,

00:01:09.596 --> 00:01:13.382
most people would think that
that's a pretty big coincidence.

00:01:13.382 --> 00:01:17.576
All right, okay, so we wanna know,
for example, we might want to ask.

00:01:17.576 --> 00:01:22.065
How many people do you need in order to
have at least a 50/50 chance that two

00:01:22.065 --> 00:01:24.184
people will have the same birthday?

00:01:24.184 --> 00:01:26.400
We want to answer questions like that,
okay?

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:28.383
So that's called the Birthday Problem.

00:01:28.383 --> 00:01:33.601
So just to state it in general,
